<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f1087363729501754714>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/journal2.html?user=313995&mid=1087363729501754714>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/journal2.html?user=313995&mid=1087363729501754714>Defeating the Prime Avatars</a> <a id=fs8 href=/journal2.html?user=313995&mid=1087363729501754714#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jun 16th 1:28 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=313995><span id=Sage>Lord TheSquall</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>43 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.65]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p><span class=lg>Guide to Defeating the Prime Avatars</span class=lg><br>By -TheSquall- <br>Please leave comments<br><br>Alright I saw a guide on here about defeating the Level 20 avatars and although it was good, I felt that it would be nice to add another guide here as well for people that may be having problems with the other guide (<a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/guides.html?guide=223 target=akztarg>Click for Hikigaeru's Guide</a>).<br><br>Please read this guide in its entirity and if you have any questions at all, please post them or email me (TheSquall@Allakhazam.com) before attempting this, just because the items cost a lot (well, they add up) and losing money sucks.<br><br>Over the past two days (well, really one because I fought the first one at like 3 AM and the rest in the afternoon), I have fought six of the avatars and defeated five of them first try. I managed to die to Ifrit because of Carbuncle doing 100 damage to Ifrit instead of 200, but it is fine. I bought some new equipment for the battle next time I fight it.<br>Out of the five I have defeated, I have set the record on my server for four of the battles and I was off by a few seconds on the last. My average time for defeating the summon is around 3 Minutes 40 Seconds.<br><br>I am going to just bang through this quickly because there are many other guides on leveling summoner to twenty and all of that good stuff.. I would like to say about the Summoning Magic skill that it does NOT have to be maxed out.. Mine's at 26 out of 63 and I have had no problems at all.<br><br><u>Food to Buy</u>: Prices I give will be on the Odin Server (My server)<br><b>1-2 Hi-Potions</b> (just in case you get hit with a 2-hour by mistake). Each Hi-Potion recovers 100 HP and cost about 1.5k Each<br><b>2 Ethers</b> Yes plain Ethers, not Hi-ethers. Each Ether recovers 20 MP and cost about 1.4k Each<br><b>1 Yagudo Drink</b> The fight should last less than 3 minutes once you use the drink so you only need one. Each Yagudo Drink recovers 3MP every tic for 3 minutes and cost about 1.2k Each<br><b>1 Boiled Crab</b> This will help your defense for when you do need to get hit, it also raises Vitality. Each Boiled Crab raises Defense 22%, Vitality 5, lasts 30 minutes, and cost (I think) 6k per Stack<br><br><u>Equipment to Use</u>:<br>Find any equipment that will raise Vitality, Evasion, Hit Points, or Defense. Watch out for elemental effects (I had a Bomb Ring and was fighting Ifrit.. Bomb Rings have +15 HP which is nice but -5 Fire Defense). I also suggest a Hermit's Wand (or anything else that will reduce Spell Interruption). I'll list my equipment that I used here:<br><b>Weapon</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=208 target=akztarg>Hermit's Wand</a> - Level 13, 6 Damage, 216 Delay, INT +2, MND +2, Spell Interruption down 25%<br><b>Ammunition</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=4705 target=akztarg>Happy Egg</a> - Level 01, 1 Damage, 777 Delay, HP +1%, VIT +1<br><b>Head</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=655 target=akztarg>Cotton Headband</a> - Level 14, 3 Defense, Evasion +3<br><b>Neck</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=662 target=akztarg>Justice Badge</a> - Level 7, 1 Defense, MND +3... I forgot to buy a new neckpiece.. I would suggest a <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=674 target=akztarg>Bloodbead Amulet</a> - Level 20, HP +15<br><b>Earrings</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=778 target=akztarg>Shield Earring</a> - Level 20, HP +10, MP -10<br><b>Body</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=432 target=akztarg>Priest's Robe</a> - Level 19, 14 Defense, MND +1, Darkness Defense +2<br><b>Hands</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=659 target=akztarg>Scentless Armlets</a> - Level 16, 4 Defense, Evasion +5<br><b>Ring</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=2003 target=akztarg>Bomb Ring</a> - Level 16, 2 Defense, HP +15, Fire Defense -5<br><b>Ring</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=750 target=akztarg>Bastokan Ring</a> - Level 01, HP +3, DEX +1, VIT +1.. Find a ring that suits you if you're not from Bastok<br><b>Back</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=726 target=akztarg>Cotton Cape</a> - Level 18, 2 Defense<br><b>Waist</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=721 target=akztarg>Silver Obi +1</a> - Level 20, 3 Defense, Spell Interruption down 8%<br><b>Legs</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=409 target=akztarg>Mage's Slacks</a> - Level 20, 11 Defense, INT +1<br><b>Feet</b>: <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?fitem=413 target=akztarg>Light Soleas</a> - Level 13, 4 Defense, Evasion +3<br>I'm going to say yes this equipment did cost a bit so that's why I was saying that you should find what you like best. Don't get anything with +mp because you're never going to use it.<br><br><u>Rumors?</u>:<br>I have heard rumors that the Summon is weak on the elemental weak day, and it sounds reasonable but I have yet to see any difference in damage done on an elemental weak or strong day.<br><br><u>Getting to the Avatar</u>:<br>You need Fame 3 in the city that you are going to be getting the avatar from (or so I hear).. To find out your fame level and how to raise fame, check out <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/forum.html?forum=11&amp;mid=1075687192334166459 target=akztarg>Tekbub's Guide to Fame</a>.. Tekbub's my idol for fame even though I have higher fame than him... *sigh*<br>Here's the locations of who you need to find for the Prime Avatar<br><b>Garuda</b> - Wind - G-8(Rabao) - &quot;Rahi Fohlatti&quot;<br><b>Ifrit</b> - Fire - J-9(Kazham) - &quot;Dodmos&quot;<br><b>Leviathan</b> - Water - H-9(Norg) - &quot;Verctissa&quot;<br><b>Shiva</b> - Ice - E-7(N. San d'Oria) - &quot;Castilchat&quot;<br><b>Titan</b> - Earth - I-8(Port Bastok) - &quot;Ferrol&quot;<br><b>Ramuh</b> - Lightning - I-9(Mhuara) - &quot;Lacia&quot;<br><br><u>Macros</u>:<br>I used an entirely blank set of macros so that I wouldn't hit anything by accident and waste time. The brackets are using the HTML code for the open bracket if it just comes up as a code.. But I don't believe it will.<br><b>Control</b>:<br>1. &quot;Cure&quot; (Just in case) - /ma &quot;Cure&quot; &lt;me&gt; <i>Use as needed</i><br>2. &quot;HiPotion&quot; - /item &quot;Hi-Potion&quot; &lt;me&gt; <i>Use as needed</i><br>3. &quot;Ether&quot; - /item &quot;Ether&quot; &lt;me&gt; <i>Used twice</i><br>4. &quot;Yagudo&quot; - /item &quot;Yagudo Drink&quot; &lt;me&gt; <i>Used once</i><br>5. Blank<br>6. Blank<br>7. Blank<br>8. &quot;Crab&quot; - /item &quot;Boiled Crab&quot; &lt;me&gt; <i>Used once</i><br>9. &quot;Protect&quot; - /ma &quot;Protect&quot; &lt;me&gt; <i>Used once</i><br>0. &quot;Aquaveil&quot; - /ma &quot;Aquaveil&quot; &lt;me&gt; <i>Used once</i><br><b>Alt</b>:<br>1. &quot;Carbuncl&quot; - /ma &quot;Carbuncle&quot; &lt;me&gt; <i>Used three times</i><br>2. &quot;Assault&quot; - /pet &quot;Assault&quot; &lt;t&gt; <i>Used once</i><br>3. &quot;SearLght&quot; - /pet &quot;Searing Light&quot; &lt;t&gt; <i>Used three times</i><br>4. &quot;AstralFl&quot; - /ja &quot;Astral Flow&quot; &lt;me&gt; <i>Used once</i><br>5. Blank<br>6. Blank<br>7. Blank<br>8. Blank<br>9. Blank<br>0. Blank<br><br><u>Time for Battle</u>:<br>I'll list what I did in order from the starting NPC to the crystal trade. Keep in mind I was using SMN20/WHM10.. Some people use different sub jobs (warrior for defense.. etc) but I just find that WHM is best imo because of Aquaveil. Although I suggest if you're going to do ANYTHING for a subjob, sub Ninja and buy another Hermit's Wand.<br><br>1. Trade the Trial Size Crystal to the appropriate NPC<br>2. Select Ready for Fight<br>3. Get warped to the cloister<br>4. Run to the cloister but don't touch it<br>5. Eat the boiled crab (Ctrl-8)<br>6. Cast Protect (Ctrl-9)<br>7. Cast Aquaveil (Ctrl-0)<br>8. If fighting Titan or Leviathan, cast Barstonra or Barwatera on yourself<br>9. TRADE the Trial Size Crystal to the Cloister. *NOTE* Do not just talk to the Cloister.. Doing so will throw you into the level 60 battle where you will DIE!<br>10. Cut-Scene<br><br><u>You're In!</u>:<br>Read this section over very carefully and multiple times. You should be able to perform this strategy without having to read the guide by the time you go into the battle. I will refer to three areas, <b>Spawn</b>, where you first arrive, <b>Middle</b>, where the right-angle turn is, and <b>Crystal</b>, where the avatar begins. Also, as a note. NEVER panic.. If you did something wrong, either try to make it better, or die. I have willfully died a couple times because I messed up. You do not lose EXP for fighting the Summons so it's alright.<br><br>1. Upon entering the battlefield, run to the <b>Middle</b>. Upon arriving, turn the 90 degrees and run one or two seconds up that path.<br>2. Cast Carbuncle (Alt-1)<br>3. Drink your Yagudo Drink (Ctrl-4)<br>4. Run most of the way to the <b>Crystal</b>, and keep hitting the 0 key on the number pad (or the F8 key), to target the enemy.<br>5. When the path begins to slowly open up, Assault the avatar (Alt-2). Try not to aggro the avatar because that will make Carbuncle run more and it will take longer, but if you do, don't worry.<br>6. When the avatar is hitting Carbuncle, run up to the summon and hit Astral Flow (Alt-4)<br>7. Stay next to the avatar (you may be getting hit now), and use Searing Light (Alt-3)<br>8. Once you see Carbuncle jump up, run for your life back towards <b>Spawn</b> - Searing Light should hit for about 210HP<br>9. Pay attention to Carbuncle's health. The moment that he gets low, stop (you should be near <b>Spawn</b>) and wait for him to die. Immediately cast Carbuncle (Alt-1) again<br>10. Wait for the avatar to come to you, Carbuncle will run after it so you do not have to Assault it again.<br>11. While Carbuncle runs to the avatar, use an Ether (Ctrl-3). When the two meet, they should probably be half way between <b>Spawn</b> and <b>Middle</b><br>12. Once the avatar is busy with Carbuncle, run up and use Searing Light, staying near the avatar just like in the beginning. If there is a wait timer, just count down the seconds and use it. <i>Please Note, you MUST have at least 44 MP for Searing Light to work. If you do not have this amount, you will waste a casting of SL and may possibly die</i> - If done right, Searing Light should hit for about 210HP<br>13. Once Carbuncle jumps again, run back towards the <b>Crystal</b>, watching Carbuncle's health again. It should be quicker to go down this time, so don't worry.<br>14. Try to get to the giant area and cast Carbuncle the moment he dies.<br>15. Wait for the avatar and Carbuncle to meet again. They should be near the <b>Crystal</b>, just about where you first assaulted the avatar. While waiting, use another Ether (Ctrl-3)<br>16. When you have over 44 MP, run up to the avatar and try to use Searing Light (Alt-3) again. I have been too quick for the timer (60 seconds) and usually have had to wait 10 seconds for Searing Light to be available. Just sit back and wait (counting down) for the timer to go down if you have this problem and use Searing Light (Alt-3) ASAP. Stand next to the avatar and watch it die.<br><br>The combined damage of three Searing Lights all critically hitting (210 each) have easily taken down the avatars. The times I have died, I have either forgotten about the 44 MP for Searing Light or the Searing Light has done ~100 Damage to the avatar. Because I have the WHM sub I don't really have much defense if I have to melee.. So this is the &quot;caster's method&quot; of killing a summon. I'm not sure how much time the <a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/db/guides.html?guide=223 target=akztarg>other method</a> takes to kill an avatar, but it seems that casting Carbuncle numerous times is overkill when you can use Searing Light three times to take it down. Plus the guide saying, &quot;Carby will probably die a couple times through this; keep calm and resummon,&quot; does not help too much in positioning of yourself to avoid getting hit. Again, my opinion.<br><br>I hope this guide helps you out, and remember to give me an email at TheSquall@Allakhazam.com or post a comment here if you have any questions..<br><br>If you think this guide helped out, please Rate it a 5 =) Thanks. Here are my times on Odin in order of completion so you can compare them to your server's times (in which my times will probably seem really long):<br><br><b>Titan</b>: 3 Minutes 46 Seconds (No Record Set.. Yes I know it's long)<br><b>Shiva</b>: 3 Minutes 40 Seconds (Record Set)<br><b>Leviathan</b>: 3 Minutes 37 Seconds (Record Set)<br><b>Garuda</b>: 3 Minutes 50 Seconds (Record Set... is Garuda hard to have 3:50 be a record?)<br><b>Ramuh</b>: 3 Minutes 36 Seconds (Record Set)<br><b>Ifrit</b>: As of June 15, 2004 I have not beat Ifrit. I'll get him on the 16th though.<br><br><i><span class=sm>Edited, Wed Jun 16 01:16:38 2004 by TheSquall</span class=sm></i></p>&nbsp;<br>-<b><a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?4742 target=akztarg>TheSquall</a> <span style='color: orange;'>Bastokan Hume Male</span style='color: orange;'> <span style='color: red;'>Rank 5</span style='color: red;'> Odin Server <a href=HTTP://www.ffrebirth.tk target=akztarg>Rebirth</a><br>45BLM/23DRG/21SMN/11WHM/10THF/9DRK/8NIN/7WAR/6BRD/2RNG/1BST<br><a href=HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/forum.html?forum=11&mid=1075687192334166459 target=akztarg>Fame</a>: Maxed Out: <span style='color: orange;'>Bastok: 9, San d'Oria: 9, Windurst: 9, Jeuno: 9, Rabao: 9, Kazham: 9, Norg: 9</span style='color: orange;'><br><br>Rate My Posts If They Are Helpful!</b></td></tr>
